JOHANNESBURG - Retail trade sales increased by 1.9 percent year-on-year in May 2018 and 1.1 percent month-on-month in May compared with April, Statistics South Africa (StatsSA) said on Wednesday. The highest annual growth rates were 14.4 percent for retailers in household furniture, appliances and equipment; 9.7 percent for all 'other' retailers; and 4.1 percent for retailers in textiles, clothing, footwear and leather goods. StatsSA said that in the three months ended May, seasonally adjusted retail trade sales decreased by 0.1 percent compared with the previous three months. But retail trade sales increased by 2.4 percent in the three months ended May 2018 compared with the three months ended May 2017. - African News Agency (ANA)